This paper is about domain adaptation for semantic segmentation using adversarial learning. The primary focus is on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (LG) techniques for semantic segmentation. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial learning (AI) and multi-level networks (MM) to improve the performance of the adapted model. Finally, the paper uses neural networks (NE) as the primary tool for the proposed method. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
